Get historical market data for symbols

get_market_data.Rd

Get historical market data for symbols

Usage

get_market_data(
  symbols = NULL,
  from = NULL,
  to = NULL,
  frequency = NULL,
  delay = 0,
  retries = 3
)

Arguments

symbols

A character vector of one or more pair symbol (required - default NULL).

from

A character with valid date/datetime format, or date/datetime object as a start of datetime range (required - default NULL).

to

A character with valid date/datetime format, or date/datetime object as an end of datetime range (required - default NULL).

frequency

A character vector of one which specify the frequency option, see details for further information (required - default NULL).

delay

A numeric value to delay data request in milliseconds (optional - default 0).

retries

A numeric value to specify the number of retries in case of failure (optional - default 3).

Value

A data.table with price data

Details

There are several supported frequencies:

  • "1 minute"

  • "3 minutes"

  • "5 minutes"

  • "15 minutes"

  • "30 minutes"

  • "1 hour"

  • "2 hours"

  • "4 hours"

  • "6 hours"

  • "8 hours"

  • "12 hours"

  • "1 day"

  • "1 week"

—————

For more information see documentation: KuCoin - get-klines

Examples


# get one symbol
kucoin::get_market_data(
    symbols = "BTC/USDT",
    from = "2022-11-05 00:00:00",
    to = "2022-11-06 00:00:00",
    frequency = "1 hour"
)
